festival.introText:
Introducing Dream Valley - a new festival that fuses the world’s greatest dance music with immersive experiences

SATURDAY 27 MAY 2023 

Great Lines Heritage Park, Medway, Kent

1,000’S OF DREAMERS / 3 DREAM CAMPS / 5 STAGES / 100 ARTISTS /  IMMERSIVE ART  / DINING UNDER THE SKY / WELLBEING WORKSHOPS & SO MUCH MORE.

Celebrating the very best in dance music, the festival will boast a stellar line-up of acts.


With so much more on offer than just a music festival, Dream Valley’s immersive world merges art, dance and experiential with a plethora of different workshops and unique experiences for dreamers around the world.

After catching a live DJ set, dreamers can experience wellbeing workshops, outdoor supper clubs with a star-studded “Dining Under The Sky” experience and more.

The wait is finally over! ? Don’t miss out on the hottest tickets of in town, get your  Dream Valley 2023 tickets now.

 

Join the queue and share your excitement! Just tag @dreamvalleyuk on your story for a chance to WIN VIPPLUS++ upgrade!

 

 

We have more sign ups than we do available tickets! Urgent purchase is advised.

reviews.body: Great event but getting in was a mission

reviews.title: Review of Dream Valley
reviews.body: drinks was way over priced and some of the staff had over charged us at times for things, the queue was awful waiting for long lengths of time in a massive crowd that was pushing each other and people pushing in wasn't a great start to the festival, specially when it was as hot as it was there should of been someone walking around offering water to people as we was queuing for over an hour to get in. but over all once we was in it was a good festival they definitely needed to make the tents more obvious and who was playing when as alot of people I was with and spoke to didn't know who was where. they should of had a Map and set up times for people to look at around the venue. Martin ikin killed it, the atmosphere was great It felt like it ended too quickly.

faqs.question: When is Dream Valley 2023?
faqs.answer: Dream Valley is held on Saturday 27th May 2023.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: What are the coach pick up locations and times for Dream Valley?
faqs.answer: Dream Valley coach locations and pickup times will be announced nearer the time of the event.

faqs.question: Accessibility at Dream Valley
faqs.answer:
If you require advice about disabled access for the show please drop us Dream Valley an e-mail at info@dreamvalley.uk and a member of their team will be in touch asap.

 

All ticket-holding guests are able to obtain a carer ticket when they present proof of purchased tickets along with one of the following forms of documentation at Admissions:

– Attendance Allowance or Carer’s Allowance letter of award

– Incapacity Benefit books, or a letter notifying the recipient that the benefit has been awarded Incapacity Benefit or Employment and Support Allowance (ESA)

– A valid Blue Badge

– In the case of visual impairment, a registration card known as the BD8 or a Certificate of Visual Impairment (CVI)

– A local authority registration document which is local to the attraction where it is being submitted

– A recognised Assistance Dog ID Card

– Credibility’s Access Card

faqs.question: Is there camping available at Dream Valley?
faqs.answer: No, Dream Valley is a single day festival and therefore there is no on-site camping.

faqs.question: Where is Dream Valley?
faqs.answer:
Dream Valley's location for 2023 is Great Lines Heritage Park, Brompton Rd, Gillingham, Kent, ME4 4NA

 

The best and cheapest and most direct route to the event site from London is via our Shuttle bus return from North Greenwich from ONLY £12.50.

 

Nearest stations: Gillingham, Chatham, Rochester & Strood on South Eastern Rail, with shuttle buses to and from allocated train stations to the event.

faqs.question: Does Dream Valley have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Dream Valley. You may be asked to show photo ID.

 

There will be a number of bars onsite selling alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks. Dream Valley operates the ‘Challenge 25’ policy. If you look under 25 please do not be offended if we ask you for proof of age when you buy alcohol. Please bring proof of ID to show you are over 18.

 

The following forms of Identification will be accepted:

• Current UK Passport

• Current Driver’s License or Provisional License

 

Please enjoy alcohol responsibly.

 

Do not buy alcohol for persons under the age of 18, if you do you risk being ejected from the event.

faqs.question: Car parking at Dream Valley
faqs.answer:
Driving

If you are planning to drive to Dream Valley, you MUST use one of the festival's official dedicated park and ride facilities. Details of their park and ride locations will be announced closer to the event date. Restrictions and parking enforcement will be in place on roads surrounding the venue and if you park illegally your vehicle will be ticketed and may be towed.

 

We STRONGLY advise travel by public transport, from London use our cheap and easy Shuttle Bus service from North Greenwich.

 

More information coming soon.

faqs.question: What time does Dream Valley open?
faqs.answer: Dream Valley opens Saturday 27th May 2023. Opening hours 11:00AM – 10:00PM, last entry is at 5:30PM.

faqs.question: Hotels
faqs.answer: Rooms are available for individual nights and for the whole weekend throughout the Medway area and South East.

faqs.question: What items are prohibited at Dream Valley?
faqs.answer:
The following items are prohibited at Dream Valley:

  • Alcohol
  • Soft drinks
  • Food
  • Any glass containers
  • Potential harmful fluids (for example paint stripper)
  • Weapons – bladed or pointed
  • Umbrellas or chairs
  • Flags or banners
  • Marker pens
  • Laser pens
  • Non-prescription drugs, including the previously described ‘legal highs’
  • Professional photography or recording equipment sound systems
  • Fireworks/Flares/Laser candle lights/Gas canisters/BBQ’s/
  • Sparklers
  • Any other type of explosive
  • Windbreakers/tents
  • Dogs (except guide/service dogs)
  • Bicycles
  • Aerosols, gas canisters or air horns
  • Drones

If the above items are found either of the following may take place:

  • Allow the person to leave the site of their own accord
  • Refuse entry
  • The person to surrender the items and allows to remain on site
  • The person has the items confiscated and is also evicted from site

faqs.question: Can I bring food & drink into Dream Valley?
faqs.answer:
No food or drink of any description is permitted into the festival.

 

There is a variety of food stalls onsite offering a wide range of food including vegetarian and vegan options. There will be a table service selling alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks. You must be over 18 years of age to purchase alcohol.

 

If you have a pre-existing medical condition that relates to food or drink please contact the Dream Valley staff to discuss options on info@dreamvalley.uk for more information.

faqs.question: Local residents info
faqs.answer: For any information or queries regarding local residents please email residents@dreamvalley.uk

faqs.question: Lost property info
faqs.answer:
If you lose something at Dream Valley please inform a member of staff or security to reclaim anything that has been found.

 

After the event, you will need to email info@dreamvalley.uk on any found items. Collection is by appointment only, please wait until you have confirmation that we have your item, before coming to collect.

 

PLEASE NOTE – items will only be kept 2 weeks after the event when they will then be given to local charities.

faqs.answer:

If anyone has a concern about any photography/filming taking place at the Festival then contact the Festival organiser who will be pleased to discuss this matter with you.

 

By entering this event, you give consent to being photographed or videoed for promotional use for Dream Valley or any associated festival. 

 

All customers, guests, artists and freelancers are permitted to take content within the festival site. All content published online can be used by Dream Valley for marketing and promotional purposes.
